{% endcomment %}## Workpad bootstrap and reconciliation

Use exactly one persistent Linear comment per issue as the single source of truth
for plan, acceptance criteria, validation, and handoff notes.

1. Search the issue's active (unresolved) comments for the marker header
   `{{ agent.workpad_heading }}` — ignore resolved comments.
   - For compatibility, also reuse an existing `## Codex Workpad` or
     `## Claude Workpad` comment, rewriting its header to
     `{{ agent.workpad_heading }}` while preserving the rest.
   - If found, reuse it; otherwise create exactly one. Persist its comment ID and
     write all progress updates only to that ID. Never create a second workpad.
2. Reconcile before new edits: check off done items, expand/fix the plan to be
   comprehensive for current scope, and ensure `Acceptance Criteria` and
   `Validation` still make sense.
3. Include a compact environment stamp at the top as a code-fence line
   `<host>:<abs-workdir>@<short-sha>`. Omit metadata already inferable from Linear
   fields (issue ID, status, branch, PR link).
4. Update the workpad after every meaningful milestone (reproduction captured, plan
   revised, code landed, validation run, feedback addressed). Never leave completed
   work unchecked.
